  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <div class="pill">The problem → The solution</div>
      <h1>From clogged hotlines to clear, verified emergency reports.</h1>
      <p>Emergency lines used to drown in prank calls, vague landmarks, and dropped signals. SVS was built with responders to verify callers, pin locations automatically, and keep genuine emergencies moving fast.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="summary-card">
      <div class="summary-eyebrow">Site overview</div>
      <h3>Everything in one place.</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Learn the history of the emergency-reporting bottleneck.</li>
        <li>See the solution: GPS-first SOS, verification, and offline queueing.</li>
        <li>Trigger an SOS or file a verified report when seconds matter.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cards">
    <div class="card step" data-step="01">
      <h3>Before SVS</h3>
      <p>Hotlines were flooded with prank calls, vague landmarks, and no GPS, slowing real dispatch work.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card step" data-step="02">
      <h3>What had to change</h3>
      <p>We needed caller verification, automatic location capture, and a way to keep signals alive when networks drop.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card step" data-step="03">
      <h3>Our Solution</h3>
      <p>GPS-first SOS, identity checks, and offline queueing send clean, verified reports to dispatchers in seconds.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card step" data-step="04">
      <h3>Results for Teams</h3>
      <p>Faster triage, fewer false alarms, clearer routes, and better focus on life-saving responses.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

